{"cursor":"10761","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\nIn politics, 'representation' describes how some individuals stand in for others\nor a group of others, for a certain time period. Representation usually refers\nto representative democracies, where elected officials nominally speak for their\nconstituents in the legislature. Generally, only citizens are granted\nrepresentation in the government in the form of voting rights; however, some\ndemocracies have extended this right further.\n","linknr":183,"url":"Representation_(politics)","recorded":1362669471,"links":21,"instances":["politics","division","electoral_district"],"pdf":["http://courses.smsu.edu/sgu646f/conf/SWPSA2005.pdf"],"categories":["Political terminology"],"headings":["Theories","Representation by population","Representation by area","Descriptive representation","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["riding","division"],["atlin","electoral_district"],["apportionment","politics"]],"members":["apportionment","riding","atlin"],"related":["Politics","Representative_democracy","Electoral_district","Legislature","Citizen","Hanna_Fenichel_Pitkin","Substantive_Representation","Edmund_Burke","United_States_Congress","Bicameral","United_States_Congress","Riding_(division)","1_E12_mÂ²","Nunavut","United_States_Senate","United_States_House_of_Representatives","Electoral_college","Baker_v._Carr","British_Columbia","Atlin_(electoral_district)","New_Brunswick","Nova_Scotia","Representative_sample","Women","Voting_systems","Proportional_representation","Eye_color","Random_sampling","George_W._Bush_administration","Colin_Powell","Condoleezza_Rice","Apportionm